SIMPLE: mission
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mission
<hw>Mis"sion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>missio</ets>, fr. <ets>mittere</ets>, <ets>missum</ets>, to send:
cf. F. <ets>mission</ets>. See <er>Missile</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The act of sending, or the state of being sent; a being sent or
delegated by authority, with certain powers for transacting business;
comission.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Whose glorious deeds, but in these fields of late,⟦br⟧
Made emulous <qex>missions</qex> 'mongst the gods themselves.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That with which a messenger or agent is charged; an
errand; business or duty on which one is sent; a commission.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>How to begin, how to accomplish best⟦br⟧
His end of being on earth, and <qex>mission</qex> high.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Persons sent; any number of persons appointed to
perform any service; a delegation; an embassy; <as>as, the Russian
<ex>mission</ex> to the United Nations</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><q>In these ships there should be a <qex>mission</qex> of three of
the fellows or brethren of Solomon's house.</q>
<rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>An assotiation or organization of missionaries; a
station or residence of missionaries.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>An organization for worship and work, dependent on
one or more churches.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>6.</sn> <def>A course of extraordinary sermons and services at a
particular place and time for the special purpose of quickening the
faith and zeal participants, and of converting unbelievers.</def>
<rj><au>Addis & Arnold.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>7.</sn> <def>Dismission; discharge from service.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Mission school</b></col>. <sd>(a)</sd> <cd>A school
connected with a mission and conducted by missionaries</cd>.
<sd>(b)</sd> <cd>A school for the religious instruction of children not
having regular church privileges.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Message; errand; commission;
deputation.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mission</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Mission
<hw>Mis"sion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To send on a
mission.</def> <mark>[Mostly used in the form of the past
participle.]</mark> <rj><au>Keats.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Missionary</ent>⟦br⟧
